[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1497},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F13\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F13\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F13\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F13\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl\u002F":1473,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F13\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl\u002F":1482},"\u002Fother\u002F20250513\u002F3343643828\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1455,"date":1456,"description":1457,"extension":1458,"lang":1459,"meta":1460,"navigation":1461,"path":1462,"readingMinutes":1463,"seo":1464,"standalone":1465,"stem":1466,"tags":1467,"tldr":1470,"updated":1456,"url":1471,"__hash__":1472},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl.md","No Postman? No Problem — Testing APIs with curl","8462017593",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1438},"minimark",[11,19,24,31,35,43,62,73,79,82,167,170,176,185,191,194,198,201,214,217,233,236,248,258,271,278,283,286,340,343,350,367,377,391,406,413,433,440,482,485,491,498,529,536,577,581,588,616,622,628,633,653,658,669,702,706,713,732,735,739,748,771,774,807,814,859,864,872,899,905,912,1002,1005,1009,1012,1060,1068,1072,1078,1108,1112,1121,1144,1146,1194,1196,1200,1206,1221,1226,1231,1235,1242,1259,1267,1271,1277,1294,1299,1302,1306,1309,1434],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"curl","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002FChatGPT%20Image%202025%E5%B9%B45%E6%9C%8814%E6%97%A5%20%E4%B8%8B%E5%8D%8811_01_19.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26,27,30],{},"Sometimes you can't use Postman to test an API, and you can't install other tools either — maybe you're SSH'd into a server (servers usually have no GUI). That's when ",[28,29,17],"code",{}," is your friend.",[20,32,34],{"id":33},"what-is-curl","What is curl?",[12,36,37,38,42],{},"curl is short for ",[39,40,41],"strong",{},"Client URL",". It's a network protocol tool that supports a huge range of protocols — FTP, FTPS, HTTP, HTTPS, and many more. Almost any network protocol you can think of, curl can test.",[44,45,46],"blockquote",{},[12,47,48,51,52,54,55,58,59,61],{},[39,49,50],{},"Note","\nSome people write ",[28,53,17],{},", others write ",[28,56,57],{},"cURL",". I'll stick with ",[28,60,17],{}," throughout this post.",[12,63,64,65,72],{},"You'll see curl all over the place. For example, the ",[66,67,71],"a",{"href":68,"rel":69},"https:\u002F\u002Fhexschool.github.io\u002Fec-courses-api-swaggerDoc\u002F#\u002F",[70],"nofollow","Hexschool Swagger API docs",":",[12,74,75],{},[15,76],{"alt":77,"src":78},"Swagger API testing","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002F20250514214238.png",[12,80,81],{},"At the bottom you'll see something like:",[83,84,89],"pre",{"className":85,"code":86,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","curl -X 'POST' \\\n  'https:\u002F\u002Fec-course-api.hexschool.io\u002Fv2\u002Fadmin\u002Fsignin' \\\n  -H 'accept: application\u002Fjson' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application\u002Fjson' \\\n  -d '{\n  \"username\": \"example@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"example\"\n}'\n","bash","",[28,90,91,111,119,130,140,149,155,161],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,93,96,99,103,107],"span",{"class":94,"line":95},"line",1,[92,97,17],{"class":98},"s_sBn",[92,100,102],{"class":101},"sCcAr"," -X",[92,104,106],{"class":105},"sTRMh"," 'POST'",[92,108,110],{"class":109},"sWyjQ"," \\\n",[92,112,114,117],{"class":94,"line":113},2,[92,115,116],{"class":105},"  'https:\u002F\u002Fec-course-api.hexschool.io\u002Fv2\u002Fadmin\u002Fsignin'",[92,118,110],{"class":109},[92,120,122,125,128],{"class":94,"line":121},3,[92,123,124],{"class":101},"  -H",[92,126,127],{"class":105}," 'accept: application\u002Fjson'",[92,129,110],{"class":109},[92,131,133,135,138],{"class":94,"line":132},4,[92,134,124],{"class":101},[92,136,137],{"class":105}," 'Content-Type: application\u002Fjson'",[92,139,110],{"class":109},[92,141,143,146],{"class":94,"line":142},5,[92,144,145],{"class":101},"  -d",[92,147,148],{"class":105}," '{\n",[92,150,152],{"class":94,"line":151},6,[92,153,154],{"class":105},"  \"username\": \"example@test.com\",\n",[92,156,158],{"class":94,"line":157},7,[92,159,160],{"class":105},"  \"password\": \"example\"\n",[92,162,164],{"class":94,"line":163},8,[92,165,166],{"class":105},"}'\n",[12,168,169],{},"You can copy that straight into a terminal and run it.",[12,171,172],{},[15,173],{"alt":174,"src":175},"Terminal","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002F20250514214527.png",[12,177,178,179,184],{},"Where else? In ",[66,180,183],{"href":181,"rel":182},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fother\u002F20211207\u002F427026\u002F",[70],"Postman (article in Mandarin)"," — after you test an API in Postman, click the \"Code\" button and you can see the curl equivalent.",[12,186,187],{},[15,188],{"alt":189,"src":190},"Postman","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002F20250514214815.png",[12,192,193],{},"Let's go through how to actually use it.",[20,195,197],{"id":196},"curl-syntax","curl syntax",[12,199,200],{},"curl's syntax is simple. If you're just testing a GET API, this line does it:",[83,202,204],{"className":85,"code":203,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl [URL]\n",[28,205,206],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,207,208,210],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,209,17],{"class":98},[92,211,213],{"class":212},"sMAXC"," [URL]\n",[12,215,216],{},"But in practice you'll need to pass parameters:",[218,219,220,224,227,230],"ul",{},[221,222,223],"li",{},"HTTP methods like POST, GET, PUT, DELETE",[221,225,226],{},"Headers",[221,228,229],{},"Body data",[221,231,232],{},"Other options",[12,234,235],{},"So the typical curl invocation looks like:",[83,237,239],{"className":85,"code":238,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl [options] [URL]\n",[28,240,241],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,242,243,245],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,244,17],{"class":98},[92,246,247],{"class":212}," [options] [URL]\n",[12,249,250,253,254,257],{},[28,251,252],{},"options"," are the flags you pass; ",[28,255,256],{},"URL"," is the target. Don't worry about the flags yet — I'll walk through CRUD examples.",[12,259,260,261,264,265,270],{},"I'll use Hexschool's practice TodoList API as the example. Base path: ",[28,262,263],{},"https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002F",". API docs: ",[66,266,269],{"href":267,"rel":268},"https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fdoc\u002F",[70],"here",".",[44,272,273],{},[12,274,275,277],{},[39,276,50],{},"\nSince this is a practice API, data gets wiped every day at 1:15 AM.",[279,280,282],"h3",{"id":281},"register-an-account-post-userssign_up","Register an account (POST \u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up)",[12,284,285],{},"First we need to register an account. From the docs, sign-up takes these params:",[83,287,291],{"className":288,"code":289,"language":290,"meta":88,"style":88},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","{\n  \"email\": \"example@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"example\",\n  \"nickname\": \"example\"\n}\n","json",[28,292,293,298,313,325,335],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,294,295],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,296,297],{"class":212},"{\n",[92,299,300,304,307,310],{"class":94,"line":113},[92,301,303],{"class":302},"sKpQp","  \"email\"",[92,305,306],{"class":212},": ",[92,308,309],{"class":105},"\"example@gmail.com\"",[92,311,312],{"class":212},",\n",[92,314,315,318,320,323],{"class":94,"line":121},[92,316,317],{"class":302},"  \"password\"",[92,319,306],{"class":212},[92,321,322],{"class":105},"\"example\"",[92,324,312],{"class":212},[92,326,327,330,332],{"class":94,"line":132},[92,328,329],{"class":302},"  \"nickname\"",[92,331,306],{"class":212},[92,333,334],{"class":105},"\"example\"\n",[92,336,337],{"class":94,"line":142},[92,338,339],{"class":212},"}\n",[12,341,342],{},"How do we call this with curl?",[12,344,345,346,349],{},"The ",[28,347,348],{},"-X"," flag specifies the HTTP method. We want POST, so:",[83,351,353],{"className":85,"code":352,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl -X POST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up\n",[28,354,355],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,356,357,359,361,364],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,358,17],{"class":98},[92,360,102],{"class":101},[92,362,363],{"class":105}," POST",[92,365,366],{"class":105}," https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up\n",[12,368,369,370,373,374,72],{},"To shorten it, you can drop the space: ",[28,371,372],{},"-X POST"," becomes ",[28,375,376],{},"-XPOST",[83,378,380],{"className":85,"code":379,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up\n",[28,381,382],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,383,384,386,389],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,385,17],{"class":98},[92,387,388],{"class":101}," -XPOST",[92,390,366],{"class":105},[44,392,393],{},[12,394,395,397,398,401,402,405],{},[39,396,50],{},"\nThe ",[28,399,400],{},"X"," must be uppercase. Lowercase ",[28,403,404],{},"-x"," is a different flag — it sets a proxy.",[12,407,408,409,412],{},"Now we need to tell the server we're sending JSON. The ",[28,410,411],{},"-H"," flag adds a header:",[83,414,416],{"className":85,"code":415,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\"\n",[28,417,418],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,419,420,422,424,427,430],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,421,17],{"class":98},[92,423,388],{"class":101},[92,425,426],{"class":105}," https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up",[92,428,429],{"class":101}," -H",[92,431,432],{"class":105}," \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\"\n",[12,434,435,436,439],{},"How do we pass the body? The ",[28,437,438],{},"-d"," flag:",[83,441,443],{"className":85,"code":442,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\" -d '{\n  \"email\": \"example@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"example\",\n  \"nickname\": \"example\"\n}'\n",[28,444,445,463,468,473,478],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,446,447,449,451,453,455,458,461],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,448,17],{"class":98},[92,450,388],{"class":101},[92,452,426],{"class":105},[92,454,429],{"class":101},[92,456,457],{"class":105}," \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\"",[92,459,460],{"class":101}," -d",[92,462,148],{"class":105},[92,464,465],{"class":94,"line":113},[92,466,467],{"class":105},"  \"email\": \"example@gmail.com\",\n",[92,469,470],{"class":94,"line":121},[92,471,472],{"class":105},"  \"password\": \"example\",\n",[92,474,475],{"class":94,"line":132},[92,476,477],{"class":105},"  \"nickname\": \"example\"\n",[92,479,480],{"class":94,"line":142},[92,481,166],{"class":105},[12,483,484],{},"Paste that in the terminal and the account gets created.",[12,486,487],{},[15,488],{"alt":489,"src":490},"Sign-up success","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002F20250514220226.png",[12,492,493,494,497],{},"Mini-exercise: sign-in is the same pattern. The endpoint is ",[28,495,496],{},"POST \u002Fusers\u002Fsign_in",", with this payload:",[83,499,501],{"className":288,"code":500,"language":290,"meta":88,"style":88},"{\n  \"email\": \"example@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"example\"\n}\n",[28,502,503,507,517,525],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,504,505],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,506,297],{"class":212},[92,508,509,511,513,515],{"class":94,"line":113},[92,510,303],{"class":302},[92,512,306],{"class":212},[92,514,309],{"class":105},[92,516,312],{"class":212},[92,518,519,521,523],{"class":94,"line":121},[92,520,317],{"class":302},[92,522,306],{"class":212},[92,524,334],{"class":105},[92,526,527],{"class":94,"line":132},[92,528,339],{"class":212},[12,530,531,532,535],{},"On success it returns a ",[28,533,534],{},"token",", which you'll need to authenticate other API calls. Try writing the curl yourself.",[537,538,539,543],"details",{},[540,541,542],"summary",{},"Click for the answer (try first!)",[83,544,546],{"className":85,"code":545,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_in -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\" -d '{\n  \"email\": \"example@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"example\"\n}'\n",[28,547,548,565,569,573],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,549,550,552,554,557,559,561,563],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,551,17],{"class":98},[92,553,388],{"class":101},[92,555,556],{"class":105}," https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_in",[92,558,429],{"class":101},[92,560,457],{"class":105},[92,562,460],{"class":101},[92,564,148],{"class":105},[92,566,567],{"class":94,"line":113},[92,568,467],{"class":105},[92,570,571],{"class":94,"line":121},[92,572,160],{"class":105},[92,574,575],{"class":94,"line":132},[92,576,166],{"class":105},[279,578,580],{"id":579},"verify-token-get-userscheckout","Verify token (GET \u002Fusers\u002Fcheckout)",[12,582,583,584,587],{},"This one's simpler — it's a GET, so we don't typically send a body. From the docs, you put the token from sign-in into the ",[28,585,586],{},"Authorization"," header:",[83,589,591],{"className":85,"code":590,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl -XGET https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fcheckout -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\" -H \"Authorization: {{ token }}\" # ← replace {{ token }} with the actual JWT\n",[28,592,593],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,594,595,597,600,603,605,607,609,612],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,596,17],{"class":98},[92,598,599],{"class":101}," -XGET",[92,601,602],{"class":105}," https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fcheckout",[92,604,429],{"class":101},[92,606,457],{"class":105},[92,608,429],{"class":101},[92,610,611],{"class":105}," \"Authorization: {{ token }}\"",[92,613,615],{"class":614},"sQrFR"," # ← replace {{ token }} with the actual JWT\n",[12,617,618],{},[15,619],{"alt":620,"src":621},"Verify token","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002F20250514220849.png",[12,623,624,627],{},[28,625,626],{},"[Token]"," is the token you got from sign-in — paste it in.",[12,629,345,630,632],{},[28,631,348],{}," flag here is actually optional, since GET is the default HTTP method. So you can write:",[83,634,636],{"className":85,"code":635,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fcheckout -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\" -H \"Authorization: {{ token }}\"\n",[28,637,638],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,639,640,642,644,646,648,650],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,641,17],{"class":98},[92,643,602],{"class":105},[92,645,429],{"class":101},[92,647,457],{"class":105},[92,649,429],{"class":101},[92,651,652],{"class":105}," \"Authorization: {{ token }}\"\n",[12,654,655],{},[15,656],{"alt":620,"src":657},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002F20250514221056.png",[12,659,660,661,663,664,666,667,72],{},"Side note: ",[28,662,376],{}," is also optional. curl auto-switches to POST if it detects a ",[28,665,438],{}," flag. So this works without ",[28,668,376],{},[83,670,672],{"className":85,"code":671,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Ftodos -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\" -H \"Authorization: {{ token }}\" -d '{\n  \"content\": \"Buy dinner\"\n}'\n",[28,673,674,693,698],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,675,676,678,681,683,685,687,689,691],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,677,17],{"class":98},[92,679,680],{"class":105}," https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Ftodos",[92,682,429],{"class":101},[92,684,457],{"class":105},[92,686,429],{"class":101},[92,688,611],{"class":105},[92,690,460],{"class":101},[92,692,148],{"class":105},[92,694,695],{"class":94,"line":113},[92,696,697],{"class":105},"  \"content\": \"Buy dinner\"\n",[92,699,700],{"class":94,"line":121},[92,701,166],{"class":105},[279,703,705],{"id":704},"list-all-todos-get-todos","List all todos (GET \u002Ftodos)",[12,707,708,709,712],{},"To fetch all todos, the endpoint is ",[28,710,711],{},"GET \u002Ftodos",". Same pattern as the token-check — token in the header:",[83,714,716],{"className":85,"code":715,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Ftodos -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\" -H \"Authorization: {{ token }}\"\n",[28,717,718],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,719,720,722,724,726,728,730],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,721,17],{"class":98},[92,723,680],{"class":105},[92,725,429],{"class":101},[92,727,457],{"class":105},[92,729,429],{"class":101},[92,731,652],{"class":105},[12,733,734],{},"Pretty straightforward, right?",[279,736,738],{"id":737},"create-a-todo-post-todos","Create a todo (POST \u002Ftodos)",[12,740,741,742,745,746,72],{},"To create one, endpoint is ",[28,743,744],{},"POST \u002Ftodos",". Same pattern as sign-up — body in ",[28,747,438],{},[83,749,751],{"className":288,"code":750,"language":290,"meta":88,"style":88},"{\n  \"content\": \"Buy dinner\"\n}\n",[28,752,753,757,767],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,754,755],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,756,297],{"class":212},[92,758,759,762,764],{"class":94,"line":113},[92,760,761],{"class":302},"  \"content\"",[92,763,306],{"class":212},[92,765,766],{"class":105},"\"Buy dinner\"\n",[92,768,769],{"class":94,"line":121},[92,770,339],{"class":212},[12,772,773],{},"So:",[83,775,777],{"className":85,"code":776,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Ftodos -H \"Content-Type