onse is long, use ",[28,1239,1240],{},"-o"," to write it to a file:",[83,1243,1245],{"className":85,"code":1244,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl -o google.html https:\u002F\u002Fgoogle.com\n",[28,1246,1247],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,1248,1249,1251,1254,1257],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,1250,17],{"class":98},[92,1252,1253],{"class":101}," -o",[92,1255,1256],{"class":105}," google.html",[92,1258,1220],{"class":105},[12,1260,1261,1263,1264,270],{},[28,1262,1240],{}," takes the filename. The response gets written to ",[28,1265,1266],{},"google.html",[20,1268,1270],{"id":1269},"set-a-user-agent","Set a User-Agent",[12,1272,1273,1274,72],{},"Can you set a User-Agent (tell the server who you are, what browser)? Yes — use ",[28,1275,1276],{},"-A",[83,1278,1280],{"className":85,"code":1279,"language":87,"meta":88,"style":88},"curl -A \"Mozilla\u002F5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit\u002F537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome\u002F58.0.3029.110 Safari\u002F537.3\" https:\u002F\u002Fgoogle.com\n",[28,1281,1282],{"__ignoreMap":88},[92,1283,1284,1286,1289,1292],{"class":94,"line":95},[92,1285,17],{"class":98},[92,1287,1288],{"class":101}," -A",[92,1290,1291],{"class":105}," \"Mozilla\u002F5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit\u002F537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome\u002F58.0.3029.110 Safari\u002F537.3\"",[92,1293,1220],{"class":105},[12,1295,1296,1298],{},[28,1297,1276],{}," takes the User-Agent string.",[12,1300,1301],{},"Why mention this? Because some sites restrict access based on unknown User-Agents, so you might need to spoof one.",[20,1303,1305],{"id":1304},"wrapping-up","Wrapping up",[12,1307,1308],{},"Quick reference table for everything covered:",[1310,1311,1312,1328],"table",{},[1313,1314,1315],"thead",{},[1316,1317,1318,1322,1325],"tr",{},[1319,1320,1321],"th",{},"Flag",[1319,1323,1324],{},"What it does",[1319,1326,1327],{},"Example",[1329,1330,1331,1346,1363,1377,1391,1405,1419],"tbody",{},[1316,1332,1333,1338,1341],{},[1334,1335,1336],"td",{},[28,